# RuufPro environment variables — partial reference.
#
# This file documents env vars added during ongoing development so a fresh
# checkout has a starting template. The authoritative list lives in the
# Vercel dashboard (Production / Preview / Development environments).
#
# Pre-existing vars referenced across the codebase (set in Vercel, NOT
# documented here yet): NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY,
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, GOOGLE_API_KEY, NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_KEY,
# SUPABASE_GEOSPATIAL_URL, SUPABASE_GEOSPATIAL_ANON_KEY, MODAL_LIDAR_TOKEN.

# === Phase 2 step 1 (2026-05-01): Mapbox Static Images for results-page polygon overlay ===
#
# Server-side only. Do NOT prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_ — the URL ends up in <img src>
# (visible to client) but the token itself is never bundled into client JS.
#
# Token must be:
#   - Created at https://account.mapbox.com/access-tokens
#   - Scoped to: styles:tiles, styles:read, fonts:read (no write/admin scopes)
#   - URL-restricted to: *.ruufpro.com, *.vercel.app, localhost:*
#
# When unset, the API responds with `roof_overlay.url: null` and the widget
# silently skips the overlay (rest of the response works normally).
MAPBOX_TOKEN=
